$(
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
                      Subbases for topologies
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
$)

  ${
    $d f g x y v w A $.  $d f g t u v w B $.
    subbas.1 $e |- A e. _V $.
    subbas.2 $e |- B = { x | E. y ( y C_ A /\ y e. Fin /\ x = |^| y ) } $.
    $( The collection of finite intersections of the elements of any set ` A `
       is a basis for a topology (on ` U. A ` by ~ subbas2 ).  The set ` A ` is
       called a subbasis for that topology.  Theorem for subbases in [Munkres]
       p. 82.  See ~ dffi2 for another way to express the collection of finite
       intersections. $)
    subbas $p |- B e. TopBases $=
      ( vu vt vw vv vf vg wcel cv wss wa cfn wceq w3a wex ctb wrex wral cint wi
      cin cab eleq2i vex eqeq1 3anbi3d exbidv elab sseq1 eleq1 eqeq2d 3anbi123d
      inteq cbvexv 3bitri eeanv an6 cun unss biimpi ineq12 intun syl6eqr cla4ev
      unfi unex syl3an inex1 bitr2i sylib ssid jctr eleq2 anbi12d rcla4ev sylbi
      syl2an ex exlimivv sylbir syl2anb ralrimiv rgen2a cvv df-sn snex eqeltrri
      wb csn abexssex 3simpb eximi ss2abi eqsstri ssexi isbasis2g ax-mp mpbir )
